Search key: `SB_SPEC_PROTECTED_MATERIAL_CATALOG_CLOSURE`
The public protected-material contract is a metadata and policy catalog, not a
secret store. Catalog records include protected_material_identity,
protected_material_version_identity, retention_policy_uuid, release_policy_uuid,
purge_policy_uuid, and audit/policy bindings for protected_material and
protected_material_version lifecycle operations. The user-facing
sys.information projections include sys.information.scratchbird_protected_material
and sys.information.scratchbird_protected_material_versions, and those views
return redacted metadata with no raw UUIDs or protected values.

Search key: `SB_SPEC_CLOUD_PROVIDER_CAPABILITY_REGISTRY`
CloudProviderCapabilityProfile records are first-class policy objects selected
by provider_profile_uuid. Public profiles describe local_emulator support,
identity modes, KMS/envelope modes, storage classes, routing, operator,
edge-cache/CDN, and observability capabilities. Private cluster-only flags are
represented as policy capability bits and fail closed in public builds. Public
sys.information surfaces may expose redacted provider capability metadata for
diagnostics and release evidence.

Search key: `SB_SPEC_CLOUD_DEPLOYMENT_PROFILE_SELECTOR_VALIDATION`
Cloud deployment profiles select a CloudProviderCapabilityProfile by
provider_profile_uuid before any external side effect. Unsupported provider
capabilities, private cluster-only fields, invalid local_emulator combinations,
and missing profiles are refused deterministically with provider diagnostics.

Search key: `SB_SPEC_CLOUD_IDENTITY_KMS_SECRETLESS_AUTHENTICATION`
Cloud identity and KMS policy is secretless by default. Supported identity mode
tokens are workload_identity, oidc_federation, managed_identity, iam_role, and
service_account_token. KMS/HSM references bind to protected-material version
UUIDs and envelope metadata; plaintext material must not be returned through
cloud identity or KMS APIs.

Search key: `SB_SPEC_CLOUD_STATIC_SECRET_REFUSAL_POLICY`
Static secret input is forbidden unless a future explicit policy says
otherwise. Public P1 cloud routes refuse static secret material with
SB_DIAG_CLOUD_STATIC_SECRET_FORBIDDEN, refuse missing provider or KMS profiles,
and audit denials before returning failure.

Search key: `SB_SPEC_KUBERNETES_OPERATOR_CRDS_LIFECYCLE_AUTOMATION`
The public single-node operator contract defines ScratchBirdDatabase,
ScratchBirdFilespace, ScratchBirdCloudProviderProfile, KMS profile, backup,
restore, route-policy, support-bundle, and upgrade CRDs. Cluster-oriented CRDs
or fields are absent from public builds or return deterministic cluster-only
refusal diagnostics.

Search key: `SB_SPEC_K8S_PUBLIC_SINGLE_NODE_DRY_RUN_AND_IDEMPOTENCY`
Operator dry-run planning reports deterministic lifecycle evidence without
claiming engine finality. Reconciliation is idempotent, status is evidence only,
and lifecycle commands still pass through manager/listener/server policy and
engine authority.

Search key: `SB_SPEC_EDGE_CACHE_CDN_INTEGRATION_INVALIDATION`
Edge cache tag and CDN invalidation records are catalog/policy objects. A cache
tag records class, dependency scope, redaction policy, finality mode, TTL, purge
state, provider profile, and signed stream metadata. Invalidation payloads are
redaction-safe and provider adapter failures remain external-effect delivery
state, not transaction finality.

Search key: `SB_SPEC_EDGE_INVALIDATION_AFTER_COMMIT_FINALITY_RULE`
Edge invalidation is queued only after ScratchBird has durable MGA commit evidence.
Rollback emits no invalidation. CDN delivery does not define MGA commit finality,
and pre-commit invalidation attempts are refused.
